JOHANNESBURG - "The Eskom Board wishes to announce the appointment of Mr Johnny Dladla as acting Group Chief Executive with immediate effect," an Eskom media release announced on Thursday."This follows intense consultations between the Minister and Eskom Board to arrive at a prudent choice.READ: Molefe removed as Eskom CEO"Both parties are of firm belief that Dladla s experience and expertise will stabilise Eskom in the short-term."Dladla has spent 22 years at Eskom, with "5 years as Chief Executive Officer for Eskom Enterprises and its subsidiaries, said Acting Board Chairman, Zethembe Khoza.Khoza said Dladla had demonstrated leadership, which had manifested in turnaround strategies.READ: Moody s downgrades Eskom s ratings with negative outlookHe "is a seasoned business leader with impeccable credentials. His business acumen, which includes his commendable knowledge of Eskom intricacies, will come in handy in his new role," Khoza said.Dladla, a Chartered Marketer, "has studied across a range of critical fields including finance and accounting amongst Harvard Business School, Fort Hare University, Cranfield University (UK), AAA School of Advertising and IMM," the statement noted.Minister of Public Enterprises Lynne Brown welcomed the appointment of dladla and said it would bring "further stability to Eskom and its executive team. She has urged the Board to finalise the appointment of a permanent Group Chief Executive to ensure the long-term stability to the utility. eNCA